The spokesperson of Pakistan Foreign Ministry terming the recent visit of minister of interior of the Islamic Republic of Iran to Islamabad as constructive and fruitful said that Tehran is a close friend and partner of Islamabad. At his weekly media briefing in Islamabad, responding a question regarding Ahmad Vahidi’s visit to Pakistan, Asim Iftikhar said it was an important visit and part of a constructive interaction with Tehran. “The visit of the Iranian Interior Minister had a wide agenda; there were useful consultations, high-level meetings, and, I think, it was part of the ongoing very constructive and fruitful dialogue and engagement of Pakistan with Iran,” he said. China-Argentina Mark 50 Years Of Diplomatic Relations Ukraine Leader Wants New Security Guarantees To Fix… The spokesperson went on to say, we will continue that engagement with Iran, including in the relevant mechanisms, as Iran is a close friend and partner of Pakistan. Heading a high-level security delegation, Vahidi paid a day-long visit to Pakistan on Monday in order to enhance mutual cooperation between Tehran and Islamabad.